<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-11-01T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-11-01T12:00:00-05:00" n="392" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d392">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">251.11 Insull, Samuel/36:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Chargé in Greece (<persName type="to">Morris</persName>)</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-11-01T12:00:00-05:00">November 1, 1932—noon</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>58. Ratifications of extradition treaty United States and Greece were
                                exchanged with Greek Minister today. You will promptly so inform
                                appropriate authorities and renew request you were directed to make
                                in Department’s 49, October 10, 11 a.m. for provisional arrest and
                                detention of Samuel Insull, Sr. with a view to his extradition on
                                the charges of embezzlement and larceny upon which warrants of
                                arrest have been issued in Cook County, Illinois.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>